pseudo's openat2 wrapper predates glibc adding a const qualifier to the
open_how parameter. glibc >= 2.39 (Ubuntu 24.04+) declares:

  int openat2(int, const char *, const struct open_how *, size_t);

while pseudo's generated wrapper still uses a non-const pointer, which
GCC rejects as a conflicting redeclaration:

  error: conflicting types for 'openat2'

The struct is only ever cast to (void) in the guts stub (open_how is
otherwise unimplemented, always ENOSYS), so adding const is a no-op
functionally and just matches the current glibc prototype.

Upstream-Status: Pending
Signed-off-by: yocto-xavier-nx

--- a/ports/linux/openat2/wrapfuncs.in
+++ b/ports/linux/openat2/wrapfuncs.in
@@ -1 +1 @@
-int openat2(int dirfd, const char *path, struct open_how *how, size_t size);
+int openat2(int dirfd, const char *path, const struct open_how *how, size_t size);
--- a/ports/linux/openat2/guts/openat2.c
